settings.name: starting_gender
settings.description: Determines the gender of your starting character. Limited to genders available in-game.

settings.name: starting_class
settings.description: Determines the class of your starting character.

settings.name: new_game_plus
settings.description: Determines how many levels of New Game + will be applied to your game. This drastically increases monster level and gold gain.

settings.name: level_scaling
settings.description: How much enemy levels will increase as you progress through the game compared to vanilla, in percentage.

settings.name: fairy_chests_per_zone
settings.description: Determines the number of Fairy Chests in a given zone that contain items. After these have been checked, only stat bonuses can be found in Fairy Chests.

settings.name: chests_per_zone
settings.description: Determines the number of normal (non-Fairy) Chests in a given zone that contain items. After these have been checked, only gold or stat bonuses can be found in Chests.

settings.name: universal_fairy_chests
settings.description: Whether Fairy Chest drops should be combined into a single larger pool.

settings.name: universal_chests
settings.description: Whether regular chest drops should be combined into a single larger pool.

settings.name: vendors
settings.description: Determines where to place the Blacksmith and Enchantress unlocks in logic (or start with them unlocked).

settings.name: architect
settings.description: Determines where to place the Architect unlock in logic (or start with him unlocked).

settings.name: architect_fee
settings.description: What percentage of gold drops the Architect will claim if you activate him.

settings.name: disable_charon
settings.description: Prevents Charon from taking your money when you re-enter the castle. Also removes Haggling from the Item Pool.

settings.name: require_purchasing
settings.description: Determines where you will be required to purchase equipment and runes from the Blacksmith and Enchantress before equipping them. If you disable require purchasing, Manor Renovations are scaled to take this into account.

settings.name: progressive_blueprints
settings.description: Whether blueprints will be received in order from weakest (Squire) to strongest (Dark).

settings.name: gold_gain_multiplier
settings.description: Adjusts the multiplier for gaining gold from all sources.

settings.name: number_of_children
settings.description: Determines how many descendants you can choose from on the Lineage screen between runs.

settings.name: castle_scaling
settings.description: How big the castle will be compared to vanilla, in percentage.

settings.name: challenge_boss_khidr
settings.description: Replaces the boss Khidr with the more powerful Neo Khidr.

settings.name: challenge_boss_alexander
settings.description: Replaces the boss Alexander with the more powerful Alexander IV.

settings.name: challenge_boss_leon
settings.description: Replaces the boss Ponce de Leon with the more powerful Ponce de Freon.

settings.name: challenge_boss_herodotus
settings.description: Replaces the boss Herodotus with the more powerful Astrodotus.

settings.name: health_up_pool
settings.description: How many Health Ups are in the item pool.

settings.name: mana_up_pool
settings.description: How many Mana Ups are in the item pool.

settings.name: attack_up_pool
settings.description: How many Attack Ups are in the item pool.

settings.name: magic_damage_up_pool
settings.description: How many Magic Damage Ups are in the item pool.

settings.name: armor_up_pool
settings.description: How many Armor Ups are in the item pool.

settings.name: equip_up_pool
settings.description: How many Equip Ups are in the item pool.

settings.name: crit_chance_up_pool
settings.description: How many Crit Chance Ups are in the item pool.

settings.name: crit_damage_up_pool
settings.description: How many Crit Damage Ups are in the item pool.

settings.name: free_diary_on_generation
settings.description: Allow the entryway to have a new diary entry (and thus, an additional item check) every time the castle is regenerated.

settings.name: death_link
settings.description: If one DeathLinked player dies, all of them do.
